description.4: Doris Nelson, adamant that she is better off alone than dating someone she doesn't love, is stuck daydreaming about her future romance! Will her dreams stay dreams or will she turn them into a reality?
description.5: Johnny Storm must stop Paste-Pot Pete from robbing a bank! Talk about "sticky fingers"! (note: this issue only contains the Human Torch story)
description.6: The Scarlet Beetle (a giant, irradiated bug), may have a size advantage over Ant-Man, but will he be immune to the power of DDT?
description.10: Johnny Storm investigates why newly built houses are sinking into their foundation and are being transported to the 5th Dimension! There, he finds himself battling Xemu, Dictator of the 5th Dimension who's planning a takeover of Earth! (note: this issue only contains the Human Torch story)
description.11: The first appearance of Ant-Man's most dastardly foe -- the criminally brilliant Egghead!
description.13: Rock Rorick comes to town, and is looking to start trouble with the Good Ol' Rawhide Kid!
description.18: As the Human Torch makes headlines, the Wizard blames him for his recent loss in popularity. A jealous Wizard tricks and traps the Torch in his house! (note: this issue only contains the Human Torch story)
description.19: Ant-Man meets a new foe in the Protector! But will this jewelry thief succumb to Pym's insect army?
description.23: The Destroyer threatens a new amusement park! Luckily, Human Torch: Johnny Storm is on the scene to do some razing of his own! (note: this issue only contains the Human Torch story)
description.24: Ant-Man must take down the Commies, namely Comrade X, before Soviet Russia gains dangerous intel on America!
description.26: If not for his impressive gun skills, The Kid's mental toughness would be his greatest attribute. But happens if that very part of his identity is challenged?
description.32: Ant-Man and his Pym Particles are back! And this time he's recruiting an entire army of ants!
description.37: "Regular gal" Karen struggles to be seen as more than a "pal" when it comes to boys!
description.38: Millie stars as a “Fabulous Flapper,” and more glamourous turns in this jam-packed issue!
description.40: Introducing... the Mighty Thor! The most exciting Super Hero of all time! When the Stone-Men from Saturn invade Earth, only Dr. Donald Blake can stop them -- but he stands no chance, not until he strikes a wooden stick on the ground and finds himself transformed into Thor, God of Thunder! Watch as Thor learns how to wield his hammer in battle! Only this new hero can save the Earth from being conquered!
description.42: A sci-fi writer believes he is being stalked by a monster not unlike one of his creations!
description.46: The First Appearance of the Amazing Spider-Man!  When young Peter Parker gains remarkable abilities from a radioactive spider, he must step up and try to become a hero — while also dealing with the fantastic pressures of an everyday teenager! For with great power, there must also come great responsibility!
description.47: Known for his larger-than-life identity, The Kid is truly what his nickname implies...a kid. In terms of size and stature he is small and frail. Can he find a way to make his size an afterthought, and defeat his bigger, badder antagonists?
description.48: Are giants real? They could be -- depending on the size of whoever's asking.
description.52: "The Monster in the Iron Mask!" Impervious to the atomic bomb! But he does have one MAJOR weakness...
description.53: An out of work actor delivers the best performance of his life...entirely on accident and for an audience of invading aliens!
description.54: Doctor Doom, in his very First Appearance!  The Fantastic Four's greatest nemesis is introduced in the first of many titanic battles as Victor Von Doom is out to prove that all should bow before Doom!
description.56: A handful of bizarre supernatural tales featuring: human guinea pigs in an alien's cruel experiment, a time-shifting fog, and a wheelchair-bound mermaid!
description.57: After being worked to death, a ride engineer haunts a giant roller coaster.
description.58: A tale of two feuding stepbrothers ends in tragedy, with one brother haunting the other.
description.59: From a young age, the Rawhide Kid was raised to be the best gun-wielding man in the world... until he's not. What will he do now when faced with a foe who is as good, if not better, than The Kid himself?
description.60: Shape-shifting aliens descend onto the Earth and figure out the quickest way to influence our thinking -- through our TV screens!
description.61: Our own Stan Lee and Steve Ditko are struggling with writers' block when a mysterious figure offers to help!
description.62: Is he a man, monster or both? The jury is still out on that one, but fans have decided that this cover by Jack Kirby is one of Marvel's best!
description.65: A beast is capable of holding an entire city in the palm of his hands...
description.66: An ancient Egyptian artifact comes to life!
description.67: The First Marvel Age Appearance of Namor!  The Sub-Mariner has returned! Calling upon his mighty sea creature army, he will have his revenge on the human race. It's up to the Fantastic Four to stop him.
description.70: The Monster from the lost city of Atlantis pays a visit to the surface world!
description.71: The Gorilla-Man returns! The former human wishes he could revert back to his former self after being held captive in a zoo.
description.72: Standing against the Bolton Gang and the Apaches, can The Kid free the girl, all the while keeping himself alive?!
description.73: Alien invaders send a shapeshifting scout in the form of Earth's dominant lifeform -- who knew it was the mosquito?
description.74: In "No Sign of Life," a group of space explorers is disappointed to find no living beings in a faraway galaxy...but they may not have looked hard enough!
description.76: Four bizarre supernatural tales featuring: an alien traveler from the future, a killer weed monster, space pirate Pildorr the Plunderer, and a sentient spaceship!
description.77: Several tales converge in this spook-tastic issue of Tales of Suspense! An unworthy magician meets the real-life Merlin! A witch finds herself pursued by a warlock. And Oog, the fearful creature from the cosmos, taunts his human rescuers!
description.78: An alien race attempts to conquer humankind...by unleashing a terrifying new weapon!
description.82: "The Thing that Crawled by Night" cannot stop growing! And the more it grows, the angrier it seems to get.
description.83: A man swaps brains with a gorilla. What could possibly go wrong?
description.84: Sometimes the only way to defeat the Rawhide Kid is not to outduel him, but to outsmart him. Will The Kid be able to withstand an ambush from multiple opponents all at once?
description.85: Can Death himself be stopped in his tracks by one man's machine? An inventor causes more trouble than he bargained for when he pulls off the impossible.
description.86: Everyone loves a ghost story! A swindler buys a castle so he can pass it off as a haunted house, but he might not need to create the ruse after all!
description.90: A movie producer's idea for a sci-fi epic plays out in real life.
description.91: He would rise to the title of 'Avenger', but before that, Dr. Hank Pym was the 'Man in the Ant Hill'! Ant-Man makes his comic debut in this sci-fi spectacle, penciled by Kirby. After toying with a size-reducing serum, Pym ill-advisedly tries it on himself...meeting his future insect sidekicks!
description.92: The First Appearance of the Skrulls!  THE SKRULLS ATTACK EARTH! From deep in space comes the Skrulls. A shape-changing alien race with one goal, to destroy the Fantastic Four and conquer Earth. Can Reed Richards come up with a plan to stop them in time?
description.95: From the trenches of space, he is...Insect Man! An astronaut becomes a play thing to a giant insectoid after a botched lunar mission.
description.96: Enter...the Four-Armed Men! An explorer believes that he has discovered a new race of extraterrestrials, but reality is stranger than it seems.
description.97: Witness the Kid duel a new foe, one donned in a dark outfit that leaves his face a mystery to all. Enter..."The Bat"!
description.98: A woman falsely accused of witchcraft, a thief with a time machine, and MUCH MORE!

0.text: Earth becomes a target of an alien hunter…and he’s after human subjects!

1.text: Dr. Doom impersonates Reed Richards so that he may use Richards' shrink ray to finally defeat the Fantastic Four!

2.text: More powerful! More dangerous! More uncontrollable than ever before! Here comes The Hulk! See the Hulk rage in "Beauty and the Beast!"

3.text: Witness Loki's most humiliating defeat as Thor outwits his brother with a clever plan that has to be read to be believed!

Loki, exiled from Asgard, has discovered Thor's mortal identity! As the two brothers battle on Earth, Loki pulls out all the magical stops, transforming trees into tigers, bazookas into birds and cars into ice cream! Witness Loki's most humiliating defeat as Thor outwits his brother with a net and a bag of peanuts!

7.text: This one has it all! Fashion shows, family drama, compositions about being a mayor for a day!

8.text: Is Mr. Meek truly the planet’s most dangerous man?

9.text: Thor must head overseas to rescue a group of American scientists. Plus, Jane Foster decides she loves Thor, not Donald Blake!

When American scientists are kidnapped by a foreign power, Thor rushes over international borders to save them! But how will the Thunder God respond when the scientists are held hostage, and he knows all his power may not be enough to save them? Meanwhile, Jane Foster decides she loves Thor, not Donald Blake! But aren't they the same man?

12.text: When the Fantastic Four go bankrupt, they're invited to S.M. Studios to make the movie about their life in order to recoup their funding. Little do they know that S.M. Studios is owned by one of their greatest enemies!

14.text: An American Western rolled into a comic!

15.text: The planet Earth is given an ultimatum -- to travel to stars and galaxies beyond!

16.text: The Incredible Hulk in two feature length thrills: "The Monster and the Machine" and "Mongu! Gladiator From Space!"

17.text:
Weary of his peace-loving society 300 years in the future, the Tomorrow Man has traveled back to modern times to steal a deadly cobalt bomb!
Using his power to traverse time, Thor pursues the villain into the future, determined to bring the weapon back! Featuring the first appearance of Odin!

20.text: The Puppet Master has arrived to control the Fantastic Four. What horrible things does he plan to do? And will our four heroes let the Puppet Master pull the strings that just may rip the family apart?

The Puppet Master has arrived to control the Fantastic Four. What horrible things does he plan to do? And will our four heroes let the Puppet Master pull the strings that just may rip the family apart?

21.text: What is the secret of the blue glass bottle?

22.text: Never before has the mighty Thor faced a foe as dangerous as Loki, the God of Mischief! The Thor family expands with the first appearances of Asgard, Loki and Heimdall! When Loki travels to Earth, the trickster god will stop at nothing to get revenge on his hated brother Thor, including unleashing his magic on the helpless mortals!

25.text: The Fantastic Four journey across the cosmos to Planet X. This planet on the edges of spaces needs our heroes help to save it from utter destruction.
The Fantastic Four journey across the cosmos to Planet X. This planet on the edges of spaces needs our heroes help to save it from utter destruction.

27.text: Hedy and Patsy hatch big plans poolside!

29.text: See the Hulk banished to outer space, trapped by the Ringmaster, and other thrills with the everyone's favorite Jade Giant!

30.text: Thor may have the strength to stand up to the deadly Executioner, but does Donald Blake have the courage to share his heart with the lovely nurse Jane Foster? In the tiny country of San Diablo, political leader the Executioner has developed an international reputation for cruelty!  Can Thor fight through an entire country's military forces to save the day?

33.text: Doctor Doom and the Sub-Mariner have joined forces to stop the Fantastic Four once and for all. But can the Sub-Mariner's hatred of all humans be tamed by the beauty of Sue Storm?

34.text: Is this truly the last performance of the Circus of Crime? The Kid joins up!

35.text: Kid Colt’s transformation into an outlaw is covered in this pivotal ‘ish!

36.text: Where is Linda Carter off to in such a rush?!

37.text: "Regular gal" Karen struggles to be seen as more than a "pal" when it comes to boys!

38.text: Millie stars as a “Fabulous Flapper,” and more glamourous turns in this jam-packed issue!

39.text: An assistant beekeeper is in for the sting of his life -- when he is shrunk down to insect-size!

43.text: Millie, Chili, and Toni enjoy some R&R at a summer resort!

44.text: Will Kathy Carter cut a rug at the big dance? And find a dance partner to boot?

45.text: The Tempest Twins may steal Patsy’s thunder during Bowling Night!

46.text: Jack Kirby and Steve Ditko collaborated on this cover to create what is quite possibly the most iconic image in Marvel Comics' history.  Before all the clones, symbiotes and civil wars we see Spider-Man in a simpler time doing what he does best, catching crooks and saving the day.

49.text: The Incredible Hulk in "The Terror of the Toad Men!"

54.text: Let's see, what's the most awesome thing about this issue? The first apearance of Dr. Doom? Thing wearing an eyepatch, pretending to be a pirate? Yeah, it's all pretty great.

Let's see, what's the most awesome thing about this issue? The first apearance of Dr. Doom? Thing wearing an eyepatch, pretending to be a pirate? Stan Lee and Jack Kirby starting to hit their stride? Yeah, it's all pretty great.
The Fantastic Four, has met their match. Doctor Doom, has come to make short work of our super family four.

62.text: Witness the birth of the Jade Giant! The Hulk is the strangest man alive. Is he man or monster...or both?
Is he a man, monster or both?  The jury is still out on that one, but fans have decided that this cover by Jack Kirby is one of Marvel's best!
